# An [[anthology]] of previously released material linked together by theme or author, especially in book form.
#* {{quote-book|chapter=Summation: 2002|editor={{w|Gardner Dozois}}|title=The Year’s Best Science Fiction: Twentieth Annual Collection|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:St. Martin's Press|St. Martin's Griffin]]|year=2003|page=xxvi|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=qeZ6abT7OpsC&pg=PR26|isbn=978-0-312-30859-9|passage=[[w:Orb Publications|Orb]] published an '''omnibus''' by {{w|Hal Clement}}, ''Heavy Planet'', containing his novels ''{{w|Mission of Gravity}}'' and ''{{w|Star Light}}'', plus other related material, and an '''omnibus''' of three of [[w:James White (author)|James White]]'s "{{w|Sector General}}" novels, ''Alien Emergencies'', as well as a reissue of [[w:A. E. van Vogt|A[lfred] E[lton] [v]an Vogt]]'s ''{{w|The World of Null-A}}''.}}
